# External data vs configuration

## Do not

- Embed repository files into the binary (`include_str!`, `include_bytes!`, codegen from checked-in blobs) for game/domain data shipped with the crate.
- Open or read arbitrary project files from disk at runtime (for example CSV, JSON, or other bundled assets in the repository tree) unless that path is explicitly a **configuration file locations that this application reads and writes** (for example batrs player files under `$HOME/.batrs`).

## Do instead

- Keep canonical domain lists and tables as **Rust source** (arrays, enums, structs) beside the logic that consumes them.
- Maintain optional human-readable mirrors (spreadsheet-export CSV, docs) in-repo only as documentation; duplicate structure in Rust after intentional edits.

## Allowed configuration I/O

- Reading and persisting batrs/player settings and profile data paths used by [`ConfigManager`](src/config.rs) and similar code is expected.
